      "content": "An integrity check isn't going to change the fact that the regulators want a clean slate. They're worried that your \"interconnected components\" have essentially baked in non-standard ways of interpreting regulations that aren't in the original training. They'd rather work with a predictable, base-level model than try to untangle whatever logic you've developed. Is there a specific reason you think an integrity check would change the audit's decision?",
